### Screenshot inspection artefacts ###
# Keep committed visual assets in source directories possible, but ignore
# one-off screenshots dropped at the repo root during UI inspection.
screenshots/
screenshot/
*screenshot*.png
*screenshot*.jpg
*screenshot*.jpeg
*screenshot*.webp
/*.png
/*.jpg
/*.jpeg
/*.webp

### benchmark — runtime artefacts ###
# The actual results (results/*.md), analysis (analysis/*.md), essays,
# prompts, and scripts ARE the experiment record and SHOULD be tracked.
# Only the verbose runtime logs and process bookkeeping are ignored.
benchmark/logs/*.log
benchmark/logs/*.nohup.out
benchmark/logs/*.pid

### apps/viewer — viewer build & runtime artefacts ###
apps/viewer/dist/
apps/viewer/node_modules/
apps/viewer/package-lock.json
apps/viewer/extract/extract.log

# Reviewer-process ephemera. Keep the actual review outputs
# (01-ui-codex.md / 02-ui-claude.md / 03-code-codex.md / 04-code-claude.md /
# *-prompt.md) since they document the design history.
apps/viewer/reviews/round-*.log
apps/viewer/reviews/round-*.nohup.out
apps/viewer/reviews/round-*.pid
apps/viewer/reviews/*.nohup.out

# Vite serves the parent repo through a /corpus middleware in dev.
# A leftover symlink at public/corpus would point outside the repo.
apps/viewer/public/corpus

### real-essays — source corpus ###
# Raw .docx files and parsed .md/.json outputs are project data and
# should stay visible to git.

